   138	## GitHub Webhook Receiver
   139	
   140	`POST /github/webhooks` accepts signed GitHub App webhook deliveries and acknowledges valid signed JSON events without retaining raw payloads or running event-specific product logic. Signature verification follows GitHub's `X-Hub-Signature-256` webhook signing model.
   141	
   142	Required request properties:
   143	
   144	- `Content-Type` primary media type is `application/json`
   145	- body is at most `256 KiB`
   146	- `X-GitHub-Event` is present
   147	- `X-GitHub-Delivery` is present
   148	- `X-Hub-Signature-256` is present and matches `sha256=<64 lowercase hex chars>`
   149	- `X-GitHub-Hook-Installation-Target-Type` is `integration`
   150	- `X-GitHub-Hook-Installation-Target-ID` equals configured `GITHUB_APP_ID`
   151	- body parses as JSON after signature verification
   152	
   153	Responses:
   154	
   155	- valid signed `ping`: `202 {"accepted":true,"event":"ping"}`
   156	- any other valid signed JSON event: `202 {"accepted":true}`
   157	- malformed JSON after authentication: `400` problem details
   158	- missing GitHub event, delivery, or signature header: `400` problem details
   159	- missing or wrong target app headers: `401` problem details
   160	- malformed or invalid signature: `401` problem details
   161	- body too large: `413` problem details
   162	- non-JSON content type: `415` problem details
   163	- missing webhook secret configuration: `500` problem details
   164	
   165	The receiver verifies the exact request bytes read through the bounded request-body reader. It does not store delivery ids, raw bodies, or parsed event payloads.
   166	
   167	## Runtime Bindings
   168	
   169	The implementation uses these runtime bindings:
   170	
   171	- `GITHUB_APP_ID`
   172	- `GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET` Secrets Store binding or Worker secret
   173	- `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` Secrets Store binding or Worker secret
   174	- `TOKEN_EXCHANGE_RATE_LIMIT` Cloudflare rate-limit binding
   175	
   176	The public Wrangler configs declare binding names for local development, tests, and dry-runs. `GITHUB_API_BASE_URL` is optional for the token exchange Worker and defaults to `https://api.github.com`.
   177	
   178	## Unsupported Behaviour
   179	
   180	cyspbot does not implement:
   181	
   182	- caller-selected arbitrary repositories
   183	- caller-supplied raw GitHub permissions
   184	- caller-defined GitHub permission profiles or aliases
   185	- multi-audience subject tokens or multi-resource token requests
   186	- dynamic issuer discovery from untrusted tokens
   187	- raw webhook payload archival or replay
   188	- product-specific webhook event processing
